        {
          "w": "In this lesson we learn the following:\n1. Unlike English, Arabic has three numbers: singular, plural and dual. Dual refers to two, and more than two is plural. The dual form ends in <<-âni>>, e.g.,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "mode": "vocab",
      "words": [
        { "w": "بَيْتَانِ", "e": "" },
        { "w": "بَيْتٌ", "e": "" },
        { "w": "bait-âni", "e": "" },
        { "w": "bait-u-n", "e": "" },
        { "w": "يَدَانِ", "e": "" },
        { "w": "يَدٌ", "e": "" },
        { "w": "yad-âni", "e": "" },
        { "w": "yad-u-n", "e": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "words": [
        { "w": "The dual of هَذَا is هَذَانِ and of هَذِهِ is هَاتَانِ" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "mode": "text",
      "words": [{ "w": "هَذَانِ كِتَابَانِ.    هَاتَانِ سَيَّارَتَانِ" }]
    },
    { "words": [{ "w": "The dual of هُوَ  and هِيَ is هُمَا, e.g.," }] },

    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "مَنْ هَذَانِ الْوَلَدَانِ؟" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "Who are these two boys?" }] },

    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "هُمَا طَالِبَانِ جَدِيدَانِ." }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "They are (two) new students." }] },

    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "أَينَ الأُخَتَانِ؟" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "Where are the two sisters?" }] },

    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "هُمَا فِي الغُرْفَةِ." }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "They are in the room." }] },
    {
      "words": [
        { "w": "Note that the adjective qualifying a dual noun is also dual." }
      ]
    },
    {
      "words": [
        {
          "w": "2. كَمْ \"how many\". Note that the noun following كَمْ is singular and in the accusative case, e.g.,"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "كَمْ كِتَابََا" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "How many books?" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "كَمْ سَيَّارَةََ" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "How many cars" }] },
    {
      "words": [
        {
          "w": "Note that a noun with tanwîn in the accusative case takes an alif which is not pronounced, e.g.,"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "كِتَابٌ - كِتَابٍ - كِتَابََا" }] },
    {
      "words": [
        {
          "w": "But a noun ending in the round ta (ة) does not take this alif, e.g.,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "mode": "text",
      "words": [{ "w": "سَيَّارَةٌ - سَيَّارَةٍ - سَيَّارَةََ" }]
    },
